 Wittgenstein. The articles in the book discuss why Wittgenstein wrote so intensively about colour during the last years of his life, what significance these remarks have for understanding his philosophical work in general, as well as the upshot of his thoughts on colour. Contributors to the volume are Andrew Lugg, Joachim Schulte, Gabriele Mras, Richard Heinrich, Herbert Hrachovec, Barry Stroud, Martin Kusch, Frederik Gierlinger and Gary Kemp.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aColor (Philosophy) 0aColor vision. 4aFarbstudien. 4aPhilosophie/20. Jahrhundert. 4aÄsthetik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  a20th-Century Philosophy.  aAesthetics.  aStudies on Colour.1 aGierlinger, Frederik A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGierlinger, Frederik A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeinrich, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHrachovec, Herbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemp, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKusch, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLugg, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMras, Gabriele M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiegelnik, Štefan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchulte, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStroud, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist P